3.00	Islet_of_Langerhans	Islets of Langerhans	The islets of Langerhans are the regions of the pancreas that contain its endocrine (i.e., hormone-producing) cells. Discovered in 1869 by German pathological anatomist Paul Langerhans at the age of 22, the islets of Langerhans constitute approximately 1 to 2% of the mass of the pancreas	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/Mouse_pancreatic_islet.jpg/250px-Mouse_pancreatic_islet.jpg
